LsdbAge.description: This field is the age of the link state advertisement in seconds.

LsdbAreaId.description: The 32-bit identifier of the area from which the LSA was received.

LsdbChecksum.description: This field is the checksum of the complete contents of the advertisement

LsdbLsid.description: The Link State ID is an LS Type Specific field containing either a Router ID or an IP address; it identifies the piece of the routing domain that is being described by the advertisement.

LsdbRouterId.description: The 32-bit number that uniquely identifies the originating router in the Autonomous System.

LsdbSequence.description: The sequence number field is a signed 32-bit integer.  It starts with the value '80000001'h

LsdbType.description: The type of the link state advertisement. Each link state type has a separate advertisement format.  Note
